            <title>[SEC-1073] 2.6. The Default Authentication Manager - Sentence &quot;You can&apos;t use a custom &apos;AuthenticationProvider&apos; if you are using either&quot; should be &apos;AuthenticationManager</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1073</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In section 2.6. The Default Authentication Manager - &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BEGIN QUOTE:&lt;br/&gt;
We&apos;ve touched on the idea that the namespace configuration automatically registers an authentication manager bean for you. This is an instance of Spring Security&apos;s ProviderManager class, which you may already be familiar with if you&apos;ve used the framework before. You can&apos;t use a custom AuthenticationProvider if you are using either HTTP or method security through the namespace, but this should not be a problem as you have full control over the AuthenticationProviders that are used.&lt;br/&gt;
END QUOTE&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The 3rd Sentence &quot;You can&apos;t use a custom &apos;AuthenticationProvider&apos; if you are using either ... &quot; should it be &apos;AuthenticationManager instead?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>N/A</environment>
